\pard\f0\fs28 Sect. LIGULATAE Haw. ({\i Aizoonia} Tausch). Leaves mostly basal in compact rosettes, coriaceous, usually glaucous, entire or finely toothed, usually lime-encrusted. Flowers in terminal panicles; after flowering the rosette bearing the panicle dies. Petals white, rarely orange or pink. Ovary semi-inferior to almost inferior.
\par

