\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 45. S. callosa} Sm. in Dickson,{\i  Coll. Dried Pl.}{\b  3}: no. 63 (1791). Leaves entire or feebly erose-crenate, glaucous, lime-encrusted, often dark red near the base; rosettes proliferating by short stolons which produce new rosettes. Flowering stem 15-40 cm. Flowers numerous, in a long, fairly narrow panicle, which usually occupies about ½ the flowering stem. Pedicels slender, often reddish, Petals 7-9 mm, white, often with crimson spots.{\i  Limestone rocks. • W. Mediterranean region.} Ga Hs It Sa Si.
