\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b catalaunica} (Boiss.) D.A. Webb,{\i  Feddes Repert.}{\b  68}: 208 (1963) ({\i S. catalaunica} Boiss.): Leaves 15-45 × 8-9 mm, oblanceolate, often acute. Inflorescence rather densely covered by subsessile glands. Peduncle glabrous or with glandular hairs.{\i  N.E. Spain; S.E. France} ({\i hills near Marseille}).
